    {
      "kind": "content",
      "content": [
        {
          "anchor": "overview",
          "level": 2,
          "text": "Overview",
          "type": "heading"
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Because a title bar accessory view controller is contained in a visual effect view (that is, "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsvisualeffectview"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "), it automatically handles the blur behind the accessory view and the size and location changes for the content of the view when a window goes in and out of full screen mode. If you’re currently using "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstoolbar"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " fullscreen accessory APIs, such as "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstoolbar/1516991-fullscreenaccessoryview"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", you should use "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstitlebaraccessoryviewcontroller"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " APIs instead."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Typically, you create an "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSTitlebarAccessoryViewController"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " object, give it your custom view, set the "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstitlebaraccessoryviewcontroller/1397778-layoutattribute"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property to ensure that it displays correctly in relation to the title bar, and add the view controller to your window. For more information about "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nswindow"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " methods you can use to add and remove a title bar accessory view controller, see "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nswindow#1662162"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "inlineContent": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": "Don’t override the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "view"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property in your "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "NSTitlebarAccessoryViewController"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " subclass. Instead, you can override "
            },
            {
              "type": "reference",
              "isActive": true,
              "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nsviewcontroller/1434405-loadview"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": ", and set the "
            },
            {
              "type": "codeVoice",
              "code": "view"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "text": " property in that method."
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "aside",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "paragraph",
              "inlineContent": [
                {
                  "type": "codeVoice",
                  "code": "NSTitlebarAccessoryViewController"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " observes the view's frame for changes. Depending on the value of "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstitlebaraccessoryviewcontroller/1397778-layoutattribute"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", you can change either the height or the width of the view. Specifically, you can change the view’s height when "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstitlebaraccessoryviewcontroller/1397778-layoutattribute"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/nslayoutattribute/nslayoutattributebottom"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ", and you can change the view’s width when the "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": false,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/appkit/nstitlebaraccessoryviewcontroller/1397778-layoutattribute"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " is "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/nslayoutattribute/nslayoutattributeright"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": " or "
                },
                {
                  "type": "reference",
                  "isActive": true,
                  "identifier": "doc://com.apple.documentation/documentation/uikit/nslayoutattribute/nslayoutattributeleft"
                },
                {
                  "type": "text",
                  "text": ". The remaining size direction is automatically set to the maximum size as required for the window."
                }
              ]
            }
          ],
          "style": "note",
          "name": "Note"
        }
      ]
    }
  ],
